The paper discusses a new algorithm for clustering data belonging to low-dimensional subspaces, with a focus on handling noisy and incomplete data. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for clustering data. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper uses facial images as an example dataset. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of a fast and efficient algorithm. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the handling of corrupted and incomplete data. 

cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper discusses the numerical evidence of the algorithm's performance.
